  "text": "Pathogen's basic reproduction number under helminth coinfection Equation 1 describes how a coinfecting helminth may affect the impact of a pathogen at the individual host level. However, helminths are also likely to affect the spread of the pathogen at the population level. Given the epidemiological framework above, the basic reproduction number of the pathogen (R 0,V ) is: [CITATION_1] , which describes the initial potential for spread of the pathogen through a population of susceptible hosts. Using this equation I explore how mean worm burden (M ) affects R 0,V under the various interaction scenarios described below.",
